Thanks for working on this.
There're still 4 medium priority warnings:
https://builds.apache.org/job/PreCommit-HBASE-Build/12142/artifact/patchprocess/newPatchFindbugsWarningshbase-thrift.html

So, the thing here is in ThriftHttpServlet class:


public ThriftHttpServlet(TProcessor processor, TProtocolFactory protocolFactory,

      UserGroupInformation realUser, Configuration conf, ThriftServerRunner.HBaseHandler

      hbaseHandler, boolean securityEnabled, boolean doAsEnabled) {

    super(processor, protocolFactory);

    this.realUser = realUser;

    this.conf = conf;

    this.hbaseHandler = hbaseHandler;

    this.securityEnabled = securityEnabled;

    this.doAsEnabled = doAsEnabled;

  }

Findbug is unhappy about me using realUser, conf and hbaseHandler as they are not implementing Serializable. The code is more or less inspired from this servlet implementation in hive. You have any suggestions?

How about making realUser, conf and hbaseHandler transient.
Declare ThriftHttpServlet$HttpKerberosServerAction as static inner class.

Thanks
Thanks Ted Yu for pointing out "transient" keyword. Attaching the updated patch.
Looks like QA bot didn't pick the patch up. Re-uploading it.

From https://builds.apache.org/job/PreCommit-HBASE-Build/12151/console:


There are Protoc compilation errors.

======================================================================

[ERROR] Failed to execute goal org.apache.hadoop:hadoop-maven-plugins:2.5.1:protoc (compile-protoc) on project hbase-protocol: org.apache.maven.plugin.MojoExecutionException: protoc version is 'libprotoc 2.4.1', expected version is '2.5.0' -> [Help 1]

[ERROR]

Looks like the machines are installed with wrong protobuf.
Can you run the following command:


mvn clean package findbugs:findbugs -DHBasePatchProcess

and examine the warnings in hbase-thrift module ?
